FT  21 AUG 92 / World Trade News: KLM accord
KLM Royal Dutch Airlines has won Japanese approval to boost its scheduled
services to Tokyo, Ronald van de Krol reports from Amsterdam. Japan Airlines
(JAL) can use Amsterdam's Schiphol Airport as a European hub. It is studying
onward 'feeder' flights in partnership with European airlines, including
KLM.
KLM can increase its services to Japan to 12 a week in 1995, when JAL will
be allowed 10 flights to Amsterdam a week.
